                the new ways of understanding the craft of making, in a context
                far from the Colombian rural daily life. In a rurality stripped
                of the craft of work, in a natural but artificial environment,
                located on the outskirts of Barcelona, a series of questions
                begin to take shape in relation to economic practices based on
                work in the countryside. It is in this place where the idea of
                "trade" begins to make sense in terms of its relationship with
                time, movement, landscape, architecture and the transformation
                of matter. Thus, a search for the meaning of work is proposed,
                not from the productive point of view, but from the constant and
                binding action to uninhabited and disused spaces.
